name: Warhammer 40,000 - Addon for SPYBG's Toolkit
description:
This is a Addon embedding specifically designed for use in my custom model SPYBG'S Toolkit. Since a request of one of my followers on youtube I've decided to make a LORA embedding specifically for the needs of one of the tutorials I'll be making this days, but :) for everyone who is hardcore and is following from YOUTUBE here in Civitai.

This day's I'll be making a video on youtube about the embedding in combination with my own custom model (SPYBG'S Toolkit). And i'll be showing the technique to achieve HQ Image results using the methods I've showed in THIS VIDEO

For everyone else who is a fan of Warhammer, I hope I did you some justice with this embedding.

Happy downloading everybody!

IMPORTANT!: If you rename the WH40K.safetensor file to something else, you also need to change the text in your prompt or the <lora:WH40K:1.0> command will not work!

example: renamed to warhammer4k.safetensor , prompt becomes <lora:warhammer4k:1.0>

Another important thing Don't use CFG Scale larger then 5

Lora embeddings seem to work better with values between 2 3 4, but test it out for your self's.

How to install the embedding:

  1. download the embedding and one of the preview images (this is optional)

  2. go to your local directory of stable diffusion example: (E:\stable-diffusion-webui\models\Lora)

  3. Put the WH40K.safetensors file in the Lora folder, (and if you download a image make sure to rename it to WH40K.png (so you can have previews in A1111's web UI if you use the Network Icon).

  4. Have fun!

I would highly recommend to try the embedding using SPYBG'S Toolkit for optimal results but it should work on all 1.5 models in general.

Another important thing, don't use negative prompts, with this embedding they are not needed, if you're curious copy some of the parameters from the sample images I've provided.
